# btaa-geo-api-download(1)

## NAME

btaa-geo-api download - download data for a BTAA resource

## SYNOPSIS

`btaa-geo-api download RESOURCE_ID (--best | --type TYPE) [--out DIR]`

## DESCRIPTION

Fetches download options from `/resources/{id}/downloads`, selects a direct or generated download, and streams it to disk.

## OPTIONS

- `--best`: choose the first available download.
- `--type TYPE`: choose a download by type, label, or format text.
- `--out DIR`: output directory.
- `--filename NAME`: override output filename.
- `--no-clobber`: fail if the output file already exists.

## EXAMPLES

```bash
btaa-geo-api downloads RESOURCE_ID
btaa-geo-api download RESOURCE_ID --best --out ./data
btaa-geo-api download RESOURCE_ID --type geojson --out ./data
```

## API ENDPOINTS

- `GET /api/v1/resources/{id}/downloads`
- `GET /api/v1/resources/{id}/downloads/generated/{download_type}`
- `GET /api/v1/resources/{id}/downloads/generated/{download_type}/file`
